ter.jpg|120px]]||Various 105&nbsp;mm guns\n| {{Flagu|Yugoslavia}} & Various\n| 100+<ref name=\"armstrade.sipri.org\"/>\n| Types: M56 and others.\n|-\n|[[File:H12 Type 63 multiple rocket launcher.JPG|120px]]|| [[Type 63 multiple rocket launcher|Type 63]]\n| {{Flagu|China}}\n| 30<ref name=\"armstrade.sipri.org\"/>\n| 107&nbsp;mm multiple rocket launcher (towed)\n|-\n|[[File:Obuzierul de Munte M1982 76mm.jpg|120px]]||[[76 mm mountain gun M48|M48]]\n|{{Flagu|Yugoslavia}}\n|212<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mmmilitary.blogspot.com/2011/12/m-48-76mm-mountain-gun.html|title=Myanmar Defence Weapons|author=MM|accessdate=29 November 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141225062238/http://mmmilitary.blogspot.com/2011/12/m-48-76mm-mountain-gun.html#|archive-date=25 December 2014|url-status=live|df=dmy-all|date=2011-12-21}}</ref>\n|76&nbsp;mm mountain gun\n|-\n|[[File:M101-105mm-howitzer-camp-pendleton-20050326.jpg|120px]]||[[M101 howitzer]]\n|{{Flagu|US}}\n|242{{citation needed|date=May 2014}}\n|105&nbsp;mm M2A1\n|-\n|[[File:25 Pounder Gun.JPG|120px]]||[[Ordnance QF 25 pounder]]\n|{{Flagu|UK}}\n|50<ref name=\"asiapacificdefencereporter.com\"/>\n|87.6&nbsp;mm Field gun/Howitzer\n|-\n|[[File:155HowLeftRear.jpg|120px]]|| [[M114 155 mm howitzer|KH-179]]<ref name=\"asiapacificdefencereporter.com\"/>\n|{{Flagu|South Korea}}\n|100+\n|155&nbsp;mm Howitzer\n|-\n|[[File:M-71-cannon-towed.JPG|120px]]||[[Soltam M-71|Soltam M-845P]]\n|{{Flagu|Israel}}\n|72<ref name=\"asiapacificdefencereporter.com\"/>\n|155&nbsp;mm 45 calibre towed gun howitzer\n|-\n|[[File:Ordnance bl55 140mm gun hameenlinna 1.jpg|120px]]||[[BL 5.5-inch Medium Gun]]\n|{{Flagu|UK}}\n|230?<ref name=\"asiapacificdefencereporter.com\"/>\n|140&nbsp;mm Towed\n|-\n|}\n \n===Air Defence===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:90%;\"\n! width=\"10%\"| Photo\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"|Model\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"|Origin\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"|Quantity\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"|Notes\n|-\n! style=