oth seen on Armed Forces Day Parade\n|-\n|[[File:Cascavel EE-009.JPG|120px]]||[[EE-9 Cascavel]]||[[armoured reconnaissance vehicle]]||150<ref name=\"Rus\"/>\n|| {{Flagu|Brazil}} || Sold by Israel, based in eastern Shan State and triangle regions near Thai-Myanmar border.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mmmilitary.blogspot.com/|title=Myanmar Defence Weapons|author=Mg Han|accessdate=29 November 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141221112919/http://mmmilitary.blogspot.com/#|archive-date=21 December 2014|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[File:Ferret-latrun-2.jpg|120px]]||[[Ferret armoured car|Ferret]] || [[Armored car (military)|Armoured car]] || 45<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scribd.com/doc/31514995/Asean-Defence-Yearbook-2009|title=Asean Defence Yearbook 2009|accessdate=29 November 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141202191013/https://www.scribd.com/doc/31514995/Asean-Defence-Yearbook-2009#|archive-date=2 December 2014|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> \n|| {{Flagu|UK}} ||\n|-\n|[[File:AML-90 DM-SC-91-12078.JPEG|120px]]|| [[Panhard AML]] || Armored car (military)|Armoured car || 50<ref name=\"deagel\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.deagel.com/Wheeled-Armored-Fighting-Vehicles/Panhard-AML_a000705001.aspx# |title=Wheeled Armored Fighting Vehicles |access-date=5 March 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141028045023/http://www.deagel.com/Wheeled-Armored-Fighting-Vehicles/Panhard-AML_a000705001.aspx# |archive-date=28 October 2014 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> \n|| {{Flagu|France}} || Modernized by Israel{{citation needed|date=November 2016}}\n|-\n|[[File:Humber pigMK1!2.jpg|120px]]|| [[Humber Pig]] || Armoured personnel carrier || 40<ref name=sipri /> \n|| {{Flagu|UK}} ||\n|-\n|[[File:PanhardM3old.JPG|120px]]||[[Panhard M3]]<ref name=\"mmmilitary.blogspot.com\">{{cite web|url=http://mmmilitary.blogspot.com/2012/11/blog-post.html|title=Myanmar Defence Weapons|author=MM|accessdate=29 November 2014|archive-url=https://web.arc